1 (4) The satisfaction level of participants who purchased a CSA product or
2 contract, including whether the participant would purchase a CSA product or contract in
3 the future, as reported through survey responses;
4 (5) Any data useful in determining potential reductions in KEHP healthcare costs;
5 and
6 (6) Options that would encourage the use of CSA purchases by KEHP
7 participants that align with improving health outcomes, reducing healthcare costs, and
8 providing more market viability for Kentucky farmers.
